        dc:description           "FIG. 5. — Postcranial specimens of Mastodonsauroidea collected in 1963 by A. Charig and colleagues in the Triassic (?Anisian) of Zambia (Luangwa Basin): A, partial interclavicle (NHMUK R10271) in ventral view; B, C, intercentra (NHMUK R10272-R10273) in anterior view; D, partial right scapulocoracoid (NHMUK R10274) in lateral view; E, right ilium (NHMUK R10275) in lateral view. Abbreviations: fsgl, supraglenoid fossa; sab, supracetabular buttress; sct, scapular tubercle. Scale bar: 10 cm." ;
